# Fluid typography (1440px baseline)

Design width is **1440px**. Text sizes are authored for that viewport and must scale up on wider screens (not stay capped).

## Tokens

- `--fluid-scale: max(1, 100vw / 1440px)` — scales up only above 1440px
- `--fs-13`, `--fs-14`, `--fs-16`, etc. — `calc(Npx * var(--fluid-scale))`

## When to use which pattern

**Fixed baseline (meta, labels, nav):**
```css
font-size: var(--fs-13); /* 13px @ 1440, grows on ultrawide */
```

**Responsive with mobile floor (body, descriptions):**
```css
font-size: max(14px, calc(16px * 100vw / 1440));
```

Do not use `clamp(..., max)` that caps size at 1440px (e.g. `clamp(14px, 1.111vw, 16px)`), because text stops growing on large monitors.
